    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-05-09T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-05-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="50"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.61334/175: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boding</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-05-09T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1925—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Department has received letter directly from Mercantile Bank of the Americas
                    stating that a settlement has been reached substantially as given in your 15,
                    May 6, 4 P.M.</p>
                <p>You should, however, continue to report promptly by cable any important
                    developments affecting this case.<note n="10" xml:id="d50fn10">On May 18, 4
                        p.m., the Minister informed the Department that an agreement between the
                        Mercantile Bank and the Association of Agriculturists had been signed on May
                        15 (file No. 822.61334/178).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
